1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] Good morning,sons of the Father.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] I hope you are well today.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,000
[SPEAKER_01] God is your Father.

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] And He loves you very much.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] He walks with us on our journeys.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
[SPEAKER_01] He supports us in our struggles.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
[SPEAKER_01] And He provides for all of our needs.

8
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:36,000
[SPEAKER_01] Our God is a good Father.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] I was asked today to speak a little bit about my own personal journey with God.

10
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] I guess we'll just start.

11
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] I was very young when I was born.

12
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
[SPEAKER_01] Very young.

13
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I was baptized when I was two weeks old by my uncle who was a priest.

14
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I went to a Catholic school.

15
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] I went to a Catholic church my whole life.

16
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] I had very nice parents.

17
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] Who were good faithful people.

18
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] Two beautiful sisters.

19
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] And a great dog.

20
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:47,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I would say that I always loved the Catholic faith.

21
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I think as a child, to me, God was somebody who lived way, way out there.

22
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I said my prayers, I went to church.

23
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] But God was very, very, very far away.

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:26,000
[SPEAKER_01] And as I got older, I became a teenager, and you begin to wonder, is this what I believe, or am I just doing this because my parents told me to do this?

25
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:40,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I never stopped going to church.

26
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I really began to question a lot about life and death and what is the purpose of our even being born.

27
00:02:49,000 --> 00:03:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] It was a time in our country the Vietnam War was going on.

28
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] And there was a kind of a...

29
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Everybody seemed angry.

30
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] Everybody seemed like they were looking for something.

31
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] And by this time, I was about 16 years old.

32
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I came to believe that the greatest good was freedom.

33
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:40,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I didn't understand freedom.

34
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:46,000
[SPEAKER_01] I thought freedom was, I can do whatever I want.

35
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] Nobody can tell me what to do, because I'm free.

36
00:03:52,000 --> 00:04:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] So then I even began to wonder, well then, if I want to be free, what about God?

37
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] How can I do whatever I want to do, if there's a God telling me what to do?

38
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] Kako mogu činiti što god želim, ako tamo negdje postoji Bog koji mi govori što trebam raditi?

39
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] So I never stopped believing.

40
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
[SPEAKER_01] Nikad nisam prestao vjerovati.

41
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I started to think that the world was all about me.

42
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] And gentlemen, I can assure you,

43
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:44,000
[SPEAKER_01] If you ever want to go to hell before dying,

44
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] Just make life all about you.

45
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:53,000
[SPEAKER_01] Samo učinite to da se cvijet vrti oko vas.

46
00:04:53,000 --> 00:05:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] It is the saddest, the coldest, the loneliest place for a human heart.

47
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] To je najtužnije, najhladnije i najusamljenije mjesto gdje čovječje srce može bit.

48
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,000
[SPEAKER_01] And at the age of 17,

49
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] I was absolutely miserable.

50
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] In fact, I thought maybe the world would be better off if I just was gone.

51
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:27,000
[SPEAKER_01] Trying to find a life for myself,

52
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] I felt like I lost everything.

53
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I kept trying harder and harder to be free.

54
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I went deeper and deeper into a very dark place within myself.

55
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:58,000
[SPEAKER_01] I remember it was holy Saturday night, the night before Easter.

56
