[SPEAKER_01] Više me zanima kamo idete.

425
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't know your story.

426
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,000
[SPEAKER_01] Ne zna vašu priču.

427
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I do know your destiny.

428
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] Ali znam koja je vaša sudbina.

429
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] And your destiny is to stand at the side of your brother Jesus

430
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:28,000
[SPEAKER_01] before the throne of your beloved father.

431
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] And as we make that journey in life,

432
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
[SPEAKER_01] we're being transformed.

433
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:46,000
[SPEAKER_01] And hopefully many others will be transformed

434
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] as we walk through their lives.

435
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] Another aspect of my life that happened a few years later.

436
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] I felt that I met Jesus in a different way.

437
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:15,000
[SPEAKER_01] I live in the United States.

438
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] And my family wasn't rich.

439
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] My family wasn't poor.

440
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] We were just kind of in the middle.

441
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] Many of our neighbors were wealthier than us.

442
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] And our car was a little bit older.

443
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] Our house wasn't as big.

444
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I kind of felt sorry for us.

445
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] A few years after I had that encounter with Jesus,

446
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] My cousin and I journeyed to South America.

447
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] I had never been there before.

448
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] I saw poverty in a new way.

449
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] I saw children fighting each other to eat food out of the streets.

450
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] One time, a friend and I, we bought a bone to feed a dog.

451
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] The dog looked like a skeleton.

452
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] So we went to a store and bought a bone to give to the dog.

453
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:44,000
[SPEAKER_01] The dog was very happy and running down the street with his bone.

454
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] Then we saw a man chasing the dog.

455
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:53,000
[SPEAKER_01] He literally jumped the dog.

456
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] And grabbed the bone away from the dog.

457
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] My friend and I were going to go over there and beat the man up.

458
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] And somebody stopped us.

459
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:09,000
[SPEAKER_01] And said, that man has seven children.

460
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] He cannot find work.

461
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:15,000
[SPEAKER_01] His family will eat that bone for a week.

462
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] We let him keep the bone.

463
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] I had never seen things like that before.

464
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] I remember one day there was a woman on the street begging.

465
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:40,000
[SPEAKER_01] And as I got close to give her a coin,

466
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:44,000
[SPEAKER_01] I realized she was completely blind.

467
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] And as I walked up, I said, you know, God bless you.

468
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:53,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I think I surprised her.

469
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] Because she suddenly turned and opened her eyes.

470
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:01,000
[SPEAKER_01] But she had no eyes. She was blind.

471
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] And when she opened her eyelids.

472
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] And when she opened her eyelids.

473
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] And she sat there day after day after day.

474
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] I had never seen things like that.

475
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:32,000
[SPEAKER_01] I was here during the war.

476
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] I won't speak much about it except to say that it absolutely broke my heart.

477
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] I carry a wound in me that I hope never goes away.

478
00:27:49,000 --> 00:28:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] I travel the entire world, but there's a special place in my heart for you, my brothers.

479
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Because of your history, because of what you've endured.

480
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] I've seen poverty.

481
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] I've seen suffering.

482
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] After this trip, I'll go back to the garbage dumps and work in Mexico.

483
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] Nakon što završim s ovim putovanjem, s ovom misijom, idem u Meksiko u jedno naselje kraj lagališta otpada.

484
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] But that one night in South America.

485
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:36,000
[SPEAKER_01] I just felt overwhelmed.

486
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] There's so much suffering in the world.

487
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:47,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't have enough coins for everybody.

488
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] I feel helpless.

489
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I made a decision while I was in South America.

490
00:28:57,000 --> 00:29:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't know what success means to you.

491
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] It could be athletics.

492
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] It could be a job, academics.

493
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:14,000
[SPEAKER_01] It could be music, entertainment.

494
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] Whatever success means to you.

495
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] Go for it.

496
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] Good.

497
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,000
[SPEAKER_01] Go for it.

498
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:26,000
[SPEAKER_01] But help at least one other person come that far.

499
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] If you're good at sports,

500
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] Good.

501
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] Super.

502
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,000
[SPEAKER_01] Teach a child how to kick a ball.

503
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] Can you make music?

504
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
[SPEAKER_01] Wonderful, we need it.

505
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] Could you teach somebody else maybe to play a little bit?

506
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] Are you particularly good at a subject?

507
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,000
[SPEAKER_01] Good for you.

508
00:29:56,000 --> 00:30:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Could you find somebody who you could help a little bit grow in that subject?

509
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:14,000
[SPEAKER_01] Whatever success means to you.

510
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] Go for it.

511
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] For me, success is someday to return home to heaven.

512
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:31,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I made a goal for myself.

513
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] Before I die.

514
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] Before I die.

515
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] I want to help one person on earth get this much closer to God.

516
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:46,000
[SPEAKER_01] Every day I get up.

517
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I say, God is today the day.

518
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] One person this much closer to God.

519
00:30:55,000 --> 00:31:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] That's my goal in life.

520
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] So, after encountering Jesus in this profound way on the cross.

521
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] And after encountering Jesus among the poor and the suffering in the world.

522
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:27,000
[SPEAKER_01] I'm trying to spend my life helping others come to know God.

523
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] And experience God.

524
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] And a lot of days I feel like I'm failing miserably.

525
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] But as you know, my father is good.

526
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,000
[SPEAKER_01] He forgives my weaknesses.

527
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] He provides what I need.

528
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] And he keeps calling me on.

529
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] And he keeps calling me on.

530
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] But you already know that because you have the same father.

531
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] Some years ago I had a unique opportunity to try to share the message of our father in a different way.

532
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] 1992 was the 500th anniversary of Columbus coming to the new world.

533
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:45,000
[SPEAKER_01] And to my surprise, it was a big controversy.

534
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] I didn't really think much about it.

535
00:32:52,000 --> 00:33:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] But different groups were saying, you know, you Europeans get out of here and you've ruined the life of the indigenous peoples.

536
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] It was a big protest.

537
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:14,000
[SPEAKER_01] And the US Catholic bishops wrote a pastoral letter.

538
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] And here's basically the key point.

539
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] The first thing they said.

540
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] We don't have to apologize to anyone for bringing the gospel.

541
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] for bringing the gospel.

542
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] Every human being has the right to hear the good news.

543
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] They're free to do with it what they want.

544
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,000
[SPEAKER_01] But they have a right to at least hear it.

545
00:33:51,000 --> 00:34:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] And we're not going to apologize for bringing the gospel to anyone and everyone.

546
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] And we're not going to apologize for bringing the gospel to anyone and everyone.

547
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] The second thing they said.

548
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] The second thing they said.

549
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,000
[SPEAKER_01] The second thing they said.

550
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:15,000
[SPEAKER_01] We have to admit that in those 500 years a lot of things were done not correctly.

551
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] There was slavery.

552
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:27,000
[SPEAKER_01] There were wars.

553
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:40,000
[SPEAKER_01] There were one group oppressing other groups.

554
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:41,000
[SPEAKER_01] And they said.

555
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:43,000
[SPEAKER_01] The part we played in this.

556
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:45,000
[SPEAKER_01] We must repent.

557
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] The third thing they said.

558
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] The third thing they said.

559
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:58,000
[SPEAKER_01] We need Jesus to be our reconciliation.

560
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] We can't ignore the problems.

561
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:10,000
[SPEAKER_01] But we can't only focus on the problems.

562
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] The only solution is Jesus Christ.

563
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] Who is our reconciliation.

564
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] And then the last thing they said was.

565
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] The last thing they said was.

566
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] Now is the time for new efforts in evangelization.

567
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:41,000
[SPEAKER_01] We must take the message of Jesus out to a very broken and angry world.

568
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:47,000
[SPEAKER_01] And it really spoke to my heart.

569
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] About a year earlier.

570
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] In my home state of Michigan.

571
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:58,000
[SPEAKER_01] We had a very small pilgrimage.

572
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] Godinu prije toga.

573
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] U mojoj rodnoj državi Michigan.

574
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] Imali smo jedno malo hodočašće.

575
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] We have seven diocese in my state.

576
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,000
[SPEAKER_01] Mojoj državi imamo sedam biskupija.

577
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] So we carried a cross from one diocese to the other.

578
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,000
[SPEAKER_01] Praying as we went.

579
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] Nosili smo križ od jedne biskupije do druge moleći puta.

580
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:21,000
[SPEAKER_01] And everything these bishops were describing.

581
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] We had experienced a year earlier walking with the cross.

582
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
[SPEAKER_01] I sve ovo što su biskupi opisivali u tom pismu.

583
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:31,000
[SPEAKER_01] Mi smo iskusili noseći taj križ.

584
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] So it rose in my heart.

585
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] Perhaps I should carry a cross across America.

586
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:43,000
[SPEAKER_01] I u mom srcu se probudila ideja da nosim križ preko Amerike.

587
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I'm thinking that cannot be God.

588
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] I mislim si u sebi to ne može biti od Boga.

589
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] That's just too crazy.

590
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] To je ipak preludo.

591
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't have that kind of time.

592
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't have that kind of time.

593
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] That short one about killed me.

594
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] I'm not going to do this long one.

595
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:01,000
[SPEAKER_01] Ovo jedno malo me skoro ubilo.

596
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] Kako ću napraviti ovo dugačko.

597
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] But it would not leave my mind.

598
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] It got so bad I started having dreams at night.

599
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:21,000
[SPEAKER_01] I saw a map of the United States.

600
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:28,000
[SPEAKER_01] And this cross floating over the country.

601
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] And gold light coming out from the cross wherever it went.

602
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] Then I started seeing the same thing even when I was awake.

603
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,000
[SPEAKER_01] So I thought I was going crazy.

604
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] So I went to my spiritual director.

605
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] Who was a priest.

606
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] I went to my confessor who was a priest.

607
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] I went to my men's sharing group.

608
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:10,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I went to a Catholic psychologist.

609
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Am I crazy?

610
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] Am I going nuts?

611
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] Am I going nuts?

612
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] And they didn't say oh it sounds wonderful.

613
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] They really challenged me.

614
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:28,000
[SPEAKER_01] Why do you think God is telling you to do this?

615
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] How are you going to support yourself?

616
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] How are you going to support yourself?

617
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] What about your other responsibilities?

618
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] So I had to answer to these four voices.

619
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] But each one came back and said we think you need to continue going forward.

620
00:38:55,000 --> 00:39:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] Maybe this is going to happen.

621
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] Maybe it won't happen.

622
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] But you should at least keep going forward.

623
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] So then I had to contact the United States Catholic bishops.

624
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:25,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I had to have a meeting with them.

625
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] And make a presentation to them.

626
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] And this had been in my heart for so long.

627
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:37,000
[SPEAKER_01] I remember submitting my presentation.

628
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I thought, after all this, what if they say no?

629
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] And then I thought, what if they say yes?

630
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] And actually, I was kind of hoping they were going to say thank you Mr. Murphy, but no.

631
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Then I could say to God,

632
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] Oh God, I was willing to do your work.

633
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] But those mean bishops won't let me.

634
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] Thank you, your grace.

635
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:28,000
