[SPEAKER_01] It was a heartbreaking story.

1494
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] And we, a friend was with me and we said, may we be able to pray with you.

1495
01:26:05,000 --> 01:26:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] That's fine, sure.

1496
01:26:12,000 --> 01:26:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I said, I don't know how to fix this.

1497
01:26:16,000 --> 01:26:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] But God can be with you now.

1498
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:26,000
[SPEAKER_01] So we began to pray.

1499
01:26:26,000 --> 01:26:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] And this is what he told us.

1500
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] He says, oh, I'm back in the doghouse.

1501
01:26:33,000 --> 01:26:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I'm so cold, I'm so scared.

1502
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:43,000
[SPEAKER_01] Here comes my dog.

1503
01:26:43,000 --> 01:26:45,000
[SPEAKER_01] Hey, hey, wait a minute.

1504
01:26:45,000 --> 01:26:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] That's not a dog coming in the, it's Jesus.

1505
01:26:50,000 --> 01:26:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] Jesus is coming into the doghouse with me.

1506
01:26:54,000 --> 01:26:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] Jesus is holding me.

1507
01:26:57,000 --> 01:27:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] Jesus is keeping me warm.

1508
01:27:00,000 --> 01:27:03,000
[SPEAKER_01] Men, I mean, it was a mystical experience.

1509
01:27:03,000 --> 01:27:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't know how to say it.

1510
01:27:07,000 --> 01:27:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] This memory of years ago, now, Jesus was there instead of the dog.

1511
01:27:18,000 --> 01:27:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] And before my eyes, I saw a man transformed.

1512
01:27:23,000 --> 01:27:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] It was extraordinary.

1513
01:27:30,000 --> 01:27:36,000
[SPEAKER_01] We were all sitting there just crying so hard.

1514
01:27:36,000 --> 01:27:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] A friend of mine was with me and he asked the man, do you think you'd be able to forgive your father?

1515
01:27:42,000 --> 01:27:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] He says, well, after this, I could.

1516
01:27:50,000 --> 01:27:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] But he's dead.

1517
01:27:52,000 --> 01:27:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] He's been dead for 14 years.

1518
01:27:55,000 --> 01:28:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] I said, your father stands before the throne of God.

1519
01:28:05,000 --> 01:28:16,000
[SPEAKER_01] And as we pray here today, we also are before the throne of God.

1520
01:28:16,000 --> 01:28:19,000
[SPEAKER_01] So what do we have in common?

1521
01:28:19,000 --> 01:28:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] He says, well, we're all with God.

1522
01:28:22,000 --> 01:28:24,000
[SPEAKER_01] Okay.

1523
01:28:24,000 --> 01:28:28,000
[SPEAKER_01] Why don't you tell God

1524
01:28:28,000 --> 01:28:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] And let him pass it on to your father.

1525
01:28:33,000 --> 01:28:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] Oh, okay.

1526
01:28:34,000 --> 01:28:36,000
[SPEAKER_01] Ovo može.

1527
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] And this is how we prayed.

1528
01:28:39,000 --> 01:28:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] Dear Jesus,

1529
01:28:42,000 --> 01:28:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] I was very sad and very angry about my life.

1530
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:53,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I was very angry with my father.

1531
01:28:53,000 --> 01:29:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] But now that you have come into the dog house, everything's okay.

1532
01:29:02,000 --> 01:29:08,000
[SPEAKER_01] Tell my father, I forgive him.

1533
01:29:08,000 --> 01:29:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] And tell him, I cannot wait to be there.

1534
01:29:12,000 --> 01:29:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] And to actually hug him in my arms.

1535
01:29:18,000 --> 01:29:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] Thank you, Jesus, for telling him that.

1536
01:29:22,000 --> 01:29:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] We were so emotional.

1537
01:29:29,000 --> 01:29:34,000
[SPEAKER_01] We moved on and continued the pilgrimage.

1538
01:29:34,000 --> 01:29:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] A few days later, we had gone around and come back through that town.

1539
01:29:38,000 --> 01:29:44,000
[SPEAKER_01] And I said, let's stop and visit our friend.

1540
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:51,000
[SPEAKER_01] So we went to the house.

1541
01:29:51,000 --> 01:29:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] But something was different.

1542
01:29:54,000 --> 01:29:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] All of the garbage was cleaned up.

1543
01:29:57,000 --> 01:30:00,000
[SPEAKER_01] There was plastic in the windows.

1544
01:30:00,000 --> 01:30:04,000
[SPEAKER_01] Somebody had put a brick under the couch.

1545
01:30:04,000 --> 01:30:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] The couch was level.

1546
01:30:06,000 --> 01:30:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] And there was a much younger man sitting on the couch, drinking a cup of coffee.

1547
01:30:13,000 --> 01:30:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] I figured the old man had died.

1548
01:30:23,000 --> 01:30:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] But as we walked up to ask the young man, where is the other guy?

1549
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:33,000
[SPEAKER_01] He said, oh, my brothers.

1550
01:30:33,000 --> 01:30:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] He said, oh, my brothers.

1551
01:30:35,000 --> 01:30:37,000
[SPEAKER_01] Is that you?

1552
01:30:37,000 --> 01:30:39,000
[SPEAKER_01] Is that you?

1553
01:30:39,000 --> 01:30:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] He looked 20 years younger.

1554
01:30:42,000 --> 01:30:47,000
[SPEAKER_01] He was clean, shaved, combed hair.

1555
01:30:47,000 --> 01:30:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] He looked like a different person.

1556
01:30:50,000 --> 01:30:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] He looked like a different person.

1557
01:30:54,000 --> 01:30:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] And he said, I don't exactly understand what happened the other day.

1558
01:30:59,000 --> 01:31:06,000
[SPEAKER_01] But I have never felt so happy in all of my life.

1559
01:31:06,000 --> 01:31:09,000
[SPEAKER_01] I am alive.

1560
01:31:09,000 --> 01:31:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] Look how blue the sky is.

1561
01:31:13,000 --> 01:31:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] Look how tall the mountains are.

1562
01:31:17,000 --> 01:31:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] I've never seen this before.

1563
01:31:20,000 --> 01:31:22,000
[SPEAKER_01] I'm alive.

1564
01:31:22,000 --> 01:31:26,000
[SPEAKER_01] And then he got a big smile on his face.

1565
01:31:26,000 --> 01:31:30,000
[SPEAKER_01] And he said, guess what I did yesterday.

1566
01:31:30,000 --> 01:31:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] He said, I have no idea what you did yesterday.

1567
01:31:35,000 --> 01:31:41,000
[SPEAKER_01] I went to confession and I went back to church.

1568
01:31:41,000 --> 01:31:55,000
[SPEAKER_01] The last time I was in a church was 14 years ago at my father's funeral.

1569
01:31:55,000 --> 01:31:58,000
[SPEAKER_01] And now I'm back.

1570
01:31:58,000 --> 01:32:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Brothers, there is no limit to the transformative power of God.

1571
01:32:11,000 --> 01:32:17,000
[SPEAKER_01] I don't know how desperate your life is or the life of your friends.

1572
01:32:17,000 --> 01:32:26,000
[SPEAKER_01] My experience has been this.

1573
01:32:26,000 --> 01:32:29,000
[SPEAKER_01] Don't try to fix people.

1574
01:32:29,000 --> 01:32:32,000
[SPEAKER_01] Listen to them.

1575
01:32:32,000 --> 01:32:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] Weep with them.

1576
01:32:35,000 --> 01:32:38,000
[SPEAKER_01] But there will be a moment.

1577
01:32:38,000 --> 01:32:44,000
[SPEAKER_01] When you can bring the cross into their world.

1578
01:32:44,000 --> 01:32:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] And when that moment arrives.

1579
01:32:48,000 --> 01:32:50,000
[SPEAKER_01] Very gently.

1580
01:32:50,000 --> 01:32:53,000
[SPEAKER_01] With great humility.

1581
01:32:53,000 --> 01:33:02,000
[SPEAKER_01] Tell them about somebody who knows their pain.

1582
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:05,000
[SPEAKER_01] Tell them about a father who understands.

1583
01:33:05,000 --> 01:33:11,000
[SPEAKER_01] Tell them about their brother who has done something for them.

1584
01:33:11,000 --> 01:33:12,000
[SPEAKER_01] For them.

1585
01:33:12,000 --> 01:33:13,000
[SPEAKER_01] Gentlemen.

1586
01:33:13,000 --> 01:33:18,000
[SPEAKER_01] Every one of us here is on a pilgrimage.

1587
01:33:18,000 --> 01:33:20,000
[SPEAKER_01] Is on a pilgrimage.

1588
01:33:20,000 --> 01:33:21,000
[SPEAKER_01] Gospodo.

1589
01:33:21,000 --> 01:33:23,000
[SPEAKER_01] Svaki od nas ovdje je na hodočašću.

1590
01:33:23,000 --> 01:33:32,000
[SPEAKER_01] Isus je rekao, ako me želite slijedite, uzmite svoj križ.

1591
01:33:32,000 --> 01:33:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] You don't have to walk across the country.

1592
01:33:35,000 --> 01:33:37,000
[SPEAKER_01] Ne morate hodati preko države.

1593
01:33:37,000 --> 01:33:42,000
[SPEAKER_01] You have to walk into the hearts and the lives of the people around you.

1594
01:33:42,000 --> 01:33:46,000
[SPEAKER_01] Morate hodati u srca i u živote ljudi oko vas.

1595
01:33:46,000 --> 01:33:49,000
[SPEAKER_01] You bring them Jesus.

1596
01:33:49,000 --> 01:33:52,000
[SPEAKER_01] Jesus will take care of the rest.

1597
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:54,000
[SPEAKER_01] Isus će se pobrenut za ostalo.

1598
01:33:54,000 --> 01:33:56,000
[SPEAKER_01] Walk on brothers.

1599
01:33:56,000 --> 01:33:57,000
[SPEAKER_01] Walk on.

1600
01:33:57,000 --> 01:33:59,000
[SPEAKER_01] Keep walking.

1601
01:33:59,000 --> 01:34:01,000
[SPEAKER_01] God bless you.

